text <- readtext("~/Documents/2021 Spring/SDS235/DC1-data/News Articles/*.txt")

data("stop_words")
#refine my word list by taking out anything related to the publisher 
mystopwords <- tibble(word = c("date", "press", "web", "published", "hawk", "copyright", "webmaster", "p.m", "a.m", "mpanni", "hawkpress.com"))

#use bigram to get more context 
text_bigram <- text %>%
  unnest_tokens(bigram, text, token = 'ngrams', n=2)

#the most counted phrases are combination of stop words 
#filter out stop words in bigrams 
bigram_separated <- text_bigram %>%
  separate(bigram, c('word1', 'word2'), sep = " ")

bigram_filtered <- bigram_separated %>%
  filter(!word1 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  filter(!word2 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  filter(!word2 %in% mystopwords$word) %>%
  filter(!word1 %in% mystopwords$word) 

#filter out numbers 
bigram_filtered_n1 <- bigram_filtered[-grep("\\b\\d+\\b", bigram_filtered$word1),]
bigram_filtered_n2 <- bigram_filtered_n1[-grep("\\b\\d+\\b", bigram_filtered_n1$word2),]

#new bigram counts 
bigram_count_n <- bigram_filtered_n2 %>%
  count(word1, word2, sort = TRUE)

#united words to a phrase
bigrams_united_n <- bigram_filtered_n2 %>%
  unite(bigram, word1, word2, sep = " ")

bigram_united_n_count <- bigrams_united_n %>%
  count(bigram, sort = TRUE) 

library(igraph)
#keep phrases that occur more than 50 times 
bi_50_count <- bigram_united_n_count%>%
   filter(n > 50)

bi_50_graph <- bigram_count_n %>%
  filter(n > 50) %>%
  graph_from_data_frame()

1 Text cleaning code is from Tidy Text Mining in R

2 Removing numbers

library(wordcloud)
set.seed(1235)
wordcloud(words = bi_50_count$bigram, freq = bi_50_count$n, min.freq = 1,
          max.words=1000, random.order=FALSE, rot.per=0.35, 
          colors=brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"))

I managed to get nice looking graphs in rmd using ‘r fig.height=4, fig.width=5’ but failed to export the graphs with the same size in html. Please refer to the pdf document to see the actual graphs.

#to dig deeper into John Torch, select articles that contain his name 
johntorch_list <- bigrams_united_n %>%
  filter(bigram == "john torch") 

jt_bigram <- text %>%
  filter(doc_id %in% c(johntorch_list$doc_id)) %>%
  unnest_tokens(bigram, text, token = 'ngrams', n=2) %>% 
  separate(bigram, c('word1', 'word2'), sep = " ") %>%
  filter(!word1 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  filter(!word2 %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  filter(!word2 %in% mystopwords$word) %>%
  filter(!word1 %in% mystopwords$word) 

jt_bigram_n1 <- jt_bigram[-grep("\\b\\d+\\b", jt_bigram$word1),]
jt_bigram_n2 <- jt_bigram_n1[-grep("\\b\\d+\\b", jt_bigram_n1$word2),]


#network graph need word 1, word 2, while word cloud need united phrase
#filter the top 100 most frequent prahses in news articles including John Torch 
jt_graph <- jt_bigram_n2 %>%
  count(word1, word2, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(100) %>%
  graph_from_data_frame()
set.seed(2021)

a <- grid::arrow(type = "closed", length = unit(.15, "inches"))

ggraph(jt_graph, layout = "fr") +
  geom_edge_link(aes(edge_alpha = n), show.legend = FALSE,
                 arrow = a, end_cap = circle(.07, 'inches')) +
  geom_node_point(color = "lightblue", size = 5) +
  geom_node_text(aes(label = name), vjust = 1, hjust = 1) +
  theme_void()
